<subSubSection id="A8D5656DA706D66A798D6EBDDA234054" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A706D66A798D6EBDDE064398" blockId="10.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
<heading id="BB38818AA706D66A798D6EBDDE064398" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" reason="3">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A706D66A798D6EBDDE064398" bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A706D66A798D6E92DA234054" blockId="10.[188,1399,447,615]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A706D66A781E6EEDDE9443EB" authority="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin, 2022" authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[302,420,448,474]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A706D66A781E6EEDDE9443EB" box="[302,420,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C988578FA706D66A789E6EEDDD3A43E8" box="[430,522,448,474]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from those of other congeners by their triangular-shaped PLP and cone-shaped anticlockwise directed embolus tip (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A706D66A7A4D6ECFDCCC43CE" box="[893,1020,482,508]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518321/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Figs 6E–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A706D66A7D3A6ECEDB6543CF" box="[1034,1109,483,509]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="13.[189,230,1829,1855]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,281,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[189,1398,266,1776]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig 7. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C. Epigynum ventral view. D. Vulva dorsal view. Abbreviations: AG = accessory gland; CO = copulatory opening; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; S = spermatheca; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518323/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">7A–B</figureCitation>
). The palp of 
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A706D66A7DCE6ECEDA4643CE" authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1278,1398,483,509]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A706D66A7DCE6ECEDA4643CE" box="[1278,1398,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A706D66A78C16D2BDC2B4012" authority="Jastrzebski 1999" authorityName="Jastrzebski" authorityYear="1999" box="[497,795,518,544]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erus">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A706D66A78C16D2BDD794012" box="[497,585,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. erus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="845E4B17A706D66A7B636D2BDC2B4012" author="Jastrzebski P." box="[595,795,518,544]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref13287" refString="Jastrzebski P. 1999. Salticidae from the Himalaya: the genus Carrhotus Thorell 1891 (Araneae, Salticidae). Senckenbergiana Biologica 9: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1999">Jastrzebski 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however, its PLP is relatively short, rounded and RTA is not pointed. RTA is smaller and tapered (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A706D66A7BD96D04DC704076" box="[745,832,553,580]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518321/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
) than in other 
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A706D66A7AD46D04DB894071" box="[996,1209,553,579]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A706D66A7AD46D04DB6C4071" box="[996,1116,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Carrhotus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="98D87676A706D66A7DCE6D04DA434071" box="[1278,1395,553,579]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. Females are distinguished by the prominent hood at the CO and hook-shaped CD (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A706D66A7DB56D61DA374054" box="[1157,1287,588,614]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="13.[189,230,1829,1855]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,281,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[189,1398,266,1776]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig 7. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C. Epigynum ventral view. D. Vulva dorsal view. Abbreviations: AG = accessory gland; CO = copulatory opening; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; S = spermatheca; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518323/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Fig. 7C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="B4B0666EA706D66A798D6887DD0C45DA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518317" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6518317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" startId="10.[189,230,1962,1988]" targetBox="[189,1398,684,1918]" targetPageId="10">
